    b"e(\"system\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Choose memory search hints for the selected task and c"
    b"urrent request.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        The hints will drive memory search before the selecte"
    b"d task runs.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once the hints look good enough for the request wit"
    b"hout thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Search surfaces:\x0d\x0a        - tags: ex"
    b"act memory tags. They are not substring searched.\x0d\x0a        - strings.contains: c"
    b"ase-insensitive text fragments. Each value is checked\x0d\x0a          as a substring "
    b"against searchable memory content.\x0d\x0a        - strings.equals: exact text values."
    b" Each value is checked for exact\x0d\x0a          equality against searchable memory c"
    b"ontent.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0d\x0a        - candidate"
    b"_memory: a vague remembered observation that could be useful to\x0d\x0a          prese"
    b"rve.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Return only search hints and optional candidat"
    b"e_memory.\x0d\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during retrieval; a memory ca"
    b"n be useful\x0d\x0a          when any positive tag or string hint matches.\x0d\x0a        - "
    b"Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0d\x0a        - Leave tags.all_of empty un"
    b"less compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0d\x0a        - Use tags.none_of onl"
    b"y for clear exclusions.\x0d\x0a        - Use strings.contains for durable words or phr"
    b"ases that should appear\x0d\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0d\x0a        - Use stri"
    b"ngs.equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0d\x0a          memory va"
    b"lue as a whole.\x0d\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints over broad ke"
    b"yword stuffing.\x0d\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful search hint is ava"
    b"ilable.\x0d\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        {{"
    b" _.role(\"user\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Current user request:\x0d\x0a        {{ current_user_req"
