    b"  {{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Choose timestamp cutoffs for each listed sea"
    b"rch domain. Your job is to quickly decide an appropriate cutoff date based on cu"
    b"rrent context.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Stop once you have timestamps that look good enough fo"
    b"r the request without thinking about it too much.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - R"
    b"eturn a SearchDepthDecision with depths and optional candidate_memory.\x0d\x0a        "
    b"- depths must contain exactly one key for each listed domain id.\x0d\x0a        - Use "
    b"the listed domain ids exactly as written.\x0d\x0a        - Each depth value must conta"
    b"in only created_after, read_after, and\x0d\x0a          updated_after ISO 8601 timesta"
    b"mp strings.\x0d\x0a        - Use the current timestamp as the reference point for rece"
    b"ncy.\x0d\x0a        - Choose each timestamp independently.\x0d\x0a        - Use older timest"
    b"amps when older context may be useful.\x0d\x0a        - Use newer timestamps when rece"
    b"nt context is enough.\x0d\x0a        - Stop once the timestamp cutoffs look good enoug"
    b"h for the request.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Timestamp fields:\x0d\x0a        - created_after: lower-"
    b"bound cutoff for created_at.\x0d\x0a        - read_after: lower-bound cutoff for read_"
    b"at.\x0d\x0a        - updated_after: lower-bound cutoff for updated_at.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Opti"
    b"onal output:\x0d\x0a        - candidate_memory: a remembered observation about choosin"
    b"g timestamp\x0d\x0a          cutoffs that could be useful later.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        {{ _.role("
    b"\"user\") }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Current timestamp:\x0d\x0a        {{ current_timestamp }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a   "
    b"     Current user request:\x0d\x0a        {{ current_user_request }}\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Select"
    b"ed task:\x0d\x0a        - id: {{ selected_task.id }}\x0d\x0a          name: {{ selected_task"
