    b"you have the right task.\x0d\x0a\x0d\x0a        Context sections:\x0d\x0a        - Current user re"
    b"quest: the request being routed now.\x0a        - Conversation history: earlier hum"
    b"an and agent messages.\x0a        - Session memories: remembered observations for t"
    b"his session.\x0a        - User preferences: durable user preferences that should in"
    b"fluence routing.\x0a        - Available tasks: the only tasks that may be selected."
    b"\x0a        - Task-choice memories: remembered observations about choosing tasks.\x0a "
    b"       - Machine state: current non-stored local time, timezone, OS/architecture"
    b",\x0a          monitor resolutions, and IP geolocation.\x0a\x0a        Optional output av"
    b"ailable in this step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation"
    b" that could be useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0d\x0a        - Select e"
    b"xactly one task from Available tasks.\x0d\x0a        - selected_task_id must exactly m"
    b"atch an available task id.\x0d\x0a        - Do not invent task ids.\x0a        - Do not p"
    b"erform the task. Only choose the task.\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when "
    b"they are useful.\x0a        - User request may be related to memories that this lay"
