    b"ontext.\x0d\x0a        - Preserve the user's goal, useful wording, preferences, constr"
    b"aints, and\x0d\x0a          unresolved details explicitly present in the supplied cont"
    b"ext.\x0d\x0a        - Translate remembered context into concrete task-relevant guidanc"
    b"e.\x0d\x0a        - Keep task_input concise and natural. Use light bullets when they m"
    b"ake it\x0d\x0a          easier to read.\x0d\x0a        - Write for the task runner using hum"
    b"an-meaningful context rather than\x0d\x0a          source bookkeeping.\x0d\x0a        - Set "
    b"candidate_memory only when this composition step reveals durable\x0d\x0a          guid"
    b"ance for future prompt composition.\x0d\x0a        - Keep a list of exact memories whe"
    b"n their contents as memories are directly related to the user request.\x0d\x0a        "
    b"- When keeping exact memories make sure to keep their parent context memory as w"
    b"ell so the structure/origin of the memory is kept even if its siblings aren't.\x0d\x0a"
